     1→# ASG Taxonomy Processing Refactoring Plan
     2→
     3→## Overview
     4→
     5→Fix critical semantic errors in taxonomy handling by eliminating string-based type checking
     6→throughout the codebase. The refactoring starts at the source (SchemaVisitor) and propagates
     7→type-safe OWL API objects through to the mapper classes.
     8→
     9→## Key Insight
    10→
    11→The OWL API already provides a well-designed type hierarchy:
    12→
    13→- `OWLObjectMinCardinality`, `OWLObjectMaxCardinality`, `OWLObjectExactCardinality` → implement
    14→  `HasCardinality`
    15→- `OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom`, `OWLObjectAllValuesFrom` → value restrictions
    16→- All implement `OWLClassExpression`
    17→
    18→**Current problem:** SchemaVisitor immediately converts these types to strings like
    19→`["someValuesFrom", ""]`, forcing all downstream code to do string comparisons.
    20→
    21→**Solution:** Keep OWL types through SchemaVisitor and only convert to strings at final output.
    22→
    23→---
    24→
    25→## Scope
    26→
    27→**In Scope:**
    28→
    29→- Refactor SchemaVisitor's public data members to use OWL types
    30→- Create `RestrictionInfo` record to carry typed restriction data
    31→- Update ResourceSchemaMapper to consume typed data
    32→- Update all mapper classes (ObjectPropertyMapper, TaxonomyPropertyMapper, DataPropertyMapper)
    33→- Fix incorrect `someValuesFrom`/`allValuesFrom` semantics (P0)
    34→- Eliminate string comparisons for restriction types
    35→
    36→---
    37→
    38→## Phase 1: Create Typed Restriction Data Structure
    39→
    40→**New File:** `src/main/java/com/grl/component/asg/RestrictionInfo.java`
    41→
    42→```java
